abstract: She said she did not want to “burn down the rest of the party” in order to triumph. And then she lost in New Hampshire.
snippet: She said she did not want to “burn down the rest of the party” in order to triumph. And then she lost in New Hampshire.
lead_paragraph: MANCHESTER, N.H. — It was 24 hours before the biggest contest of her political life. Senator Elizabeth Warren didn’t want to talk about it that way.

abstract: Amazon created a retail paradise that protects itself from critics calling for stringent regulation.
snippet: Amazon created a retail paradise that protects itself from critics calling for stringent regulation.
lead_paragraph: Amazon is a genie of consumerist wishes, and it keeps growing more irresistible. The company’s online store has always been convenient and plentiful, but in the last year, Amazon significantly increased the speed at which it delivers products, with many items delivered overnight to its Prime members. Investors on Wall Street are used to Amazon’s big spending, and many stock analysts had expected the expensive next-day shipping plan to be another loss leader. But late last month, Amazon released a stunning holiday-season earnings report that proved otherwise: Next-day shipping, the company said, had significantly boosted sales and driven many new sign-ups for Prime, which now has more than 150 million members.

abstract: U.S. central bank officials are considering options that would make it easier for banks to treat Treasury holdings similar to reserves when meeting liquidity requirements, Federal Reserve Chair Jerome Powell said this week in a letter to a top Senate Democrat.
snippet: U.S. central bank officials are considering options that would make it easier for banks to treat Treasury holdings similar to reserves when meeting liquidity requirements, Federal Reserve Chair Jerome Powell said this week in a letter to a top Sen...
lead_paragraph: (Reuters) - U.S. central bank officials are considering options that would make it easier for banks to treat Treasury holdings similar to reserves when meeting liquidity requirements, Federal Reserve Chair Jerome Powell said this week in a letter to a top Senate Democrat.
headline_main: Fed's Powell Reinforces Regulation and Defends Repo Support in Letter to Congress

abstract: Lloyd Blankfein, the former Goldman Sachs chief, tweeted an attack on Bernie Sanders after the senator’s New Hampshire primary win.
snippet: Lloyd Blankfein, the former Goldman Sachs chief, tweeted an attack on Bernie Sanders after the senator’s New Hampshire primary win.
lead_paragraph: Bernie Sanders has proposed a wealth tax on the richest Americans, criticized big businesses for turning huge profits while paying little in taxes and said he believed billionaires should not exist.
